    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This FD3S RX-7 is a superlative example of sequential twin-turbocharged engineering. The 13B-REW rotary heart delivers linear power across the rev range, with the secondary turbocharger engaging flawlessly thanks to a fully overhauled vacuum solenoid rack. Compression testing yields optimal, uniform pulses across all apex seals, ensuring long-term thermal efficiency. The chassis retains its factory-spec torsional rigidity, featuring a pristine double-wishbone suspension geometry and a Torsen limited-slip differential that maximizes corner-exit traction. Zero oxidative stress is present on the undercarriage, and the interior preserves its original tactile feedback. This is a mechanically transparent, collector-grade specimen for the discerning purist.",
